<task>
  <statement>
          <p>
            Sketch graphs of functions satisfying each of the descriptions given below.
          </p>

         <p>
            <ul>
            <li>
              <title>(I)</title>

              <p>
                The slope is positive and increasing at first, but then is positive and decreasing.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <title>(II)</title>

              <p>
                The first derivative of the function whose graph is above.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <title>(III)</title>

              <p>
                The second derivative of the first function sketched.
              </p>
            </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
  </statement>
<answer>
  <p>
    Answers vary but (I) should be increasing and concave up at first and then concave down.  (II) should be above the horizontal 
    axis and increasing and then decreasing all while being concave down.  (III) should be decreasing and passing
    through through the horizontal axis when the maximum is reached in (II). 
  </p>
</answer>
